Essentially, I've gone through a number of these tickets and noticed that some changes seem to be live in UAT, sometimes contrary to the status on the actual ticket -- hoping I can verify the status for each of these. Thank you!
it might be more helpful to comment on each of these tickets individually since there are different owners for each ticket

Thank you, I'll go ahead and do that!

In general, are tickets' statuses usually up to date? Currently, the enablement team is relying heavily on the Jira board to determine what to cover in our bi-weekly AI Hub Advancements sessions, and I certainly don't mind commenting in tickets, but I want to be sure that I proactively add the occasional check-ins to my schedule if they're regularly needed :slightly_smiling_face:

FWIW, no worries if tickets are out of date sometimes, as there's SO MUCH good going on here at Instabase  :cool-doge: :rocket:

Again, just want to make sure I set up a flow and know what to anticipate :slightly_smiling_face:

Can you provide an example of a ticket with a status that doesn’t correspond with the behavior in UAT?

if a ticket’s internal release version is 24.32, there should be a feature flag for it that’s turned on by default 

if a ticket’s external release version is 24.32, that behavior should be on for all users by default

Thank you for the insights! That's incredibly helpful :slightly_smiling_face:

Here's an example of one that was a little bit confusing --
https://instabase.atlassian.net/browse/EPD-2326

It reads `In Development` with a targeted `Fix versions` of `Release 24.32.0-aihub`, but checking UAT (24.32.0), it seems the changes described are present. :thought_balloon:
